## ­¤¤Ī FUNCTIONS & CLOSURES

### 9. Function Declarations & Expressions
- [ ] Function declarations (hoisted)
- [ ] Function expressions (not hoisted)
- [ ] Arrow functions and `this` binding
- [ ] Generator functions (`function*`)
- [ ] Async functions
- [ ] IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function Expression)
- [ ] Higher-order functions
- [ ] Currying and partial application

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Declaration vs Expression
function declared() { }        // Hoisted
const expression = function() { }; // Not hoisted

// Arrow functions
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
const square = x => x * x;     // Single param, no parens
const noop = () => undefined;  // No params, need parens

// Arrow vs regular function
const obj = {
  name: 'John',
  regularMethod: function() {
    console.log(this.name); // 'John' (this = obj)
  },
  arrowMethod: () => {
    console.log(this.name); // undefined (this = global/window)
  }
};

// IIFE - Immediately Invoked
(function() {
  let private = 'hidden';
  console.log(private);
})();
// console.log(private); // ReferenceError

// Higher-order function
function createMultiplier(factor) {
  return (number) => number * factor;
}

const double = createMultiplier(2);
console.log(double(5)); // 10

// Currying
const curry = (a) => (b) => (c) => a + b + c;
const add5 = curry(5);
const add5and10 = add5(10);
console.log(add5and10(3)); // 18
```

**Master When**: You can choose the right function type and understand this binding

---

### 10. Default Parameters & Rest/Spread
- [ ] Default parameter values
- [ ] Rest parameters (`...args`)
- [ ] Spread operator for arrays
- [ ] Spread operator for objects
- [ ] Destructuring parameters
- [ ] Arguments object vs rest parameters

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Default parameters
function greet(name = 'Guest', greeting = 'Hello') {
  return `${greeting}, ${name}!`;
}
console.log(greet()); // 'Hello, Guest!'
console.log(greet('John')); // 'Hello, John!'

// Rest parameters
function sum(...numbers) {
  return numbers.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
}
console.log(sum(1, 2, 3, 4)); // 10

// Spread operator - arrays
const arr1 = [1, 2, 3];
const arr2 = [...arr1, 4, 5];
console.log(arr2); // [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

// Spread operator - objects
const obj1 = { a: 1, b: 2 };
const obj2 = { ...obj1, c: 3 };
console.log(obj2); // { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }

// Destructuring in parameters
function displayUser({ name, age, city = 'Unknown' }) {
  console.log(`${name}, ${age}, ${city}`);
}

displayUser({ name: 'John', age: 30 });
// 'John, 30, Unknown'
```

**Master When**: You use spread/rest naturally and default parameters effectively

