## ­¤¤Ī DOM & WEB APIS

### 17. DOM Selection
- [ ] `document.getElementById()`
- [ ] `document.querySelector()` and `document.querySelectorAll()`
- [ ] `document.getElementsByClassName()` and `document.getElementsByTagName()`
- [ ] Performance considerations
- [ ] Live vs static collections
- [ ] CSS selectors

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Different selection methods
document.getElementById('main');                           // Single
document.querySelector('.header');                        // Single (CSS selector)
document.querySelectorAll('.item');                        // NodeList
document.getElementsByClassName('active');                // HTMLCollection (live)
document.getElementsByTagName('div');                      // HTMLCollection (live)

// CSS selectors in querySelector
document.querySelector('div.header > p:first-child');
document.querySelectorAll('[data-id="5"]');
document.querySelector(':not(.disabled)');

// Performance: querySelector slower but powerful
// Use getElementById if you only need IDs for better performance
```

**Master When**: You choose the right selector for performance and readability

---

### 18. DOM Manipulation
- [ ] Creating elements: `document.createElement()`, `document.createTextNode()`
- [ ] Adding elements: `appendChild()`, `insertBefore()`, `insertAdjacentHTML()`
- [ ] Removing elements: `removeChild()`, `remove()`
- [ ] Replacing elements: `replaceChild()`
- [ ] Cloning elements: `cloneNode()`
- [ ] innerHTML, textContent, innerText
- [ ] Attributes: `getAttribute()`, `setAttribute()`, `removeAttribute()`
- [ ] Data attributes: `dataset`

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Creating and adding elements
const div = document.createElement('div');
div.textContent = 'Hello';
div.className = 'greeting';
document.body.appendChild(div);

// insertAdjacentHTML (faster than innerHTML +=)
div.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', '<span>!</span>');

// Removing
div.remove();
parent.removeChild(div);

// Attributes and data
div.setAttribute('data-id', '5');
div.getAttribute('data-id');        // '5'
div.dataset.id;                     // '5' (same as above)
div.removeAttribute('data-id');

// innerHTML vs textContent
div.innerHTML = '<b>Bold</b>';      // Parses HTML
div.textContent = '<b>Bold</b>';    // Literal text

// Performance: batch operations
const fragment = document.createDocumentFragment();
for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
  const li = document.createElement('li');
  li.textContent = `Item ${i}`;
  fragment.appendChild(li); // Doesn't trigger reflow
}
list.appendChild(fragment); // Single reflow
```

**Master When**: You batch DOM operations and choose efficient methods

---

### 19. DOM Traversal
- [ ] `parentNode`, `childNodes`, `firstChild`, `lastChild`
- [ ] `nextSibling`, `previousSibling`
- [ ] `children`, `firstElementChild`, `lastElementChild`
- [ ] `nextElementSibling`, `previousElementSibling`
- [ ] `closest()` for parent matching
- [ ] NodeList vs HTMLCollection

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Node relationships
element.parentNode;          // Parent (any node)
element.parentElement;       // Parent (element only)
element.childNodes;          // All child nodes (including text)
element.children;            // Only child elements
element.firstChild;          // First node (can be text)
element.firstElementChild;   // First element

// Siblings
element.nextSibling;         // Next node (can be text)
element.nextElementSibling;  // Next element
element.previousSibling;     // Previous node

// Finding ancestor
element.closest('.container'); // First matching ancestor

// NodeList vs HTMLCollection
const nodeList = document.querySelectorAll('div');    // Static
const htmlCollection = document.getElementsByTagName('div'); // Live

// Live collection updates when DOM changes
htmlCollection.length; // Updates automatically
```

**Master When**: You navigate the DOM efficiently

---

## ­¤¤Ī EVENT HANDLING

### 20. Event Listeners
- [ ] `addEventListener()` and `removeEventListener()`
- [ ] Event listener options: `capture`, `once`, `passive`
- [ ] `addEventListener()` vs `onclick` property
- [ ] Event delegation
- [ ] Removing listeners

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Adding listeners
const button = document.querySelector('button');

button.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  console.log('Clicked');
});

// Event listener options
button.addEventListener('click', handler, {
  capture: false,   // Bubbling phase (default)
  once: true,       // Remove after first trigger
  passive: true,    // Won't call preventDefault()
});

// Event delegation
document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  if (e.target.matches('.button')) {
    console.log('Button clicked');
  }
});

// Removing listeners
button.removeEventListener('click', handler);

// Named function for removal
function clickHandler(e) {
  console.log('Clicked');
}

button.addEventListener('click', clickHandler);
button.removeEventListener('click', clickHandler);
```

**Master When**: You use event delegation and understand event listener options

---

### 21. Event Object & Methods
- [ ] Event properties: `target`, `currentTarget`, `type`, `timestamp`
- [ ] `preventDefault()`
- [ ] `stopPropagation()`
- [ ] `stopImmediatePropagation()`
- [ ] Event phases: capture, target, bubble
- [ ] `isTrusted` property

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Event object
document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
  console.log(event.type);          // 'click'
  console.log(event.target);        // Element clicked
  console.log(event.currentTarget);  // Element with listener
  console.log(event.timestamp);     // Time of event
});

// Event phases
//   1. Capture phase: from root to target
//   2. Target phase: at target
//   3. Bubble phase: from target back to root

document.addEventListener('click', () => console.log('1: capture'), true);  // Capture
document.addEventListener('click', () => console.log('2: bubble'));         // Bubble

// Result when clicking inner element:
// 1: capture
// 2: bubble

// Preventing default behavior
const link = document.querySelector('a');
link.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  e.preventDefault(); // Don't navigate
  console.log('Link clicked but didn\'t navigate');
});

// Stopping propagation
const parent = document.querySelector('.parent');
const child = document.querySelector('.child');

parent.addEventListener('click', () => {
  console.log('Parent clicked');
});

child.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  e.stopPropagation(); // Prevent bubble to parent
  console.log('Child clicked');
});

// Click child: only "Child clicked" logs
```

**Master When**: You understand event phases and use preventDefault/stopPropagation appropriately

---

### 22. Common Events
- [ ] Mouse events: `click`, `dblclick`, `mousedown`, `mouseup`, `mouseover`, `mouseout`, `mousemove`
- [ ] Keyboard events: `keydown`, `keyup`, `keypress` (deprecated)
- [ ] Form events: `submit`, `change`, `input`, `focus`, `blur`
- [ ] Window events: `load`, `unload`, `resize`, `scroll`
