## ­¤ö┤ ERROR HANDLING

### 23. Try/Catch/Finally
- [ ] Try block
- [ ] Catch block
- [ ] Finally block
- [ ] Error object properties
- [ ] Catching specific errors
- [ ] Re-throwing errors

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Basic try/catch
try {
  riskyFunction();
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Error caught:', error.message);
} finally {
  console.log('Cleanup code');
}

// Error object
try {
  throw new Error('Custom error');
} catch (error) {
  console.log(error.message);  // 'Custom error'
  console.log(error.stack);    // Stack trace
  console.log(error.name);     // 'Error'
}

// Specific error types
try {
  JSON.parse('{invalid}');
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof SyntaxError) {
    console.log('JSON syntax error');
  }
}

// Re-throwing
try {
  try {
    throw new Error('Inner error');
  } catch (error) {
    console.log('Inner catch:', error.message);
    throw error; // Re-throw
  }
} catch (error) {
  console.log('Outer catch:', error.message);
}
```

**Master When**: You handle errors appropriately and use finally for cleanup

---

### 24. Custom Errors
- [ ] Extending Error class
- [ ] Error types for different scenarios
- [ ] Error context and debugging

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Custom error class
class ValidationError extends Error {
  constructor(message, field) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'ValidationError';
    this.field = field;
  }
}

// Using custom error
try {
  if (!email) {
    throw new ValidationError('Email is required', 'email');
  }
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof ValidationError) {
    console.log(`Validation failed on ${error.field}`);
  }
}
```

**Master When**: You create custom error types for better error handling

