## ­¤ö┤ PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION

### 25. Memory Management
- [ ] Garbage collection basics
- [ ] Memory leaks
- [ ] Detached DOM nodes
- [ ] Circular references
- [ ] WeakMap and WeakSet

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Memory leak - circular reference in closures
function createLeakyObject() {
  const obj = {};
  obj.self = obj; // Circular reference
  return obj;
}

// Memory leak - event listeners
const button = document.querySelector('button');
button.addEventListener('click', function() {
  this.large = new Array(1000000); // Large data
  // Listener keeps reference forever
});

// Solution: remove listener when done
function handler() {
  console.log('clicked');
}

button.addEventListener('click', handler);
button.removeEventListener('click', handler); // Clean up

// WeakMap - doesn't prevent garbage collection
const private_data = new WeakMap();

class User {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
    private_data.set(this, { password: 'secret' });
  }
  
  getPassword() {
    return private_data.get(this).password;
  }
}

const user = new User('John');
console.log(user.getPassword()); // 'secret'
// When user is garbage collected, private_data entry is too
```

**Master When**: You identify and prevent memory leaks

---

### 26. Performance & Optimization
- [ ] Debouncing and throttling
- [ ] Lazy loading
- [ ] Pagination and virtual scrolling
- [ ] Efficient DOM queries
- [ ] Batch DOM operations
- [ ] RequestAnimationFrame
- [ ] Performance API and measuring

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Debouncing - delay execution until events stop
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timeoutId;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => fn(...args), delay);
  };
}

const handleResize = debounce(() => {
  console.log('Resized');
}, 300);

window.addEventListener('resize', handleResize);

// Throttling - limit execution frequency
function throttle(fn, delay) {
  let lastCall = 0;
  return function(...args) {
    const now = Date.now();
    if (now - lastCall >= delay) {
      fn(...args);
      lastCall = now;
    }
  };
}

const handleScroll = throttle(() => {
  console.log('Scrolled');
}, 300);

window.addEventListener('scroll', handleScroll);

// Lazy loading with Intersection Observer
const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach((entry) => {
    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
      loadImage(entry.target);
      observer.unobserve(entry.target);
    }
  });
});

document.querySelectorAll('img').forEach((img) => {
  observer.observe(img);
});

// Performance measurement
performance.mark('operation-start');
// ... do something ...
performance.mark('operation-end');
performance.measure('operation', 'operation-start', 'operation-end');

const measure = performance.getEntriesByName('operation')[0];
console.log(`Operation took ${measure.duration}ms`);
```

**Master When**: You optimize for performance and measure improvements

