## ­¤¤ó MODERN ES6+ FEATURES

### 33. Modern JavaScript Features
- [ ] Destructuring (arrays, objects, parameters)
- [ ] Template literals
- [ ] Spread operator
- [ ] Rest parameters
- [ ] Default parameters
- [ ] Arrow functions
- [ ] Enhanced object literals
- [ ] For...of loop
- [ ] Map and Set
- [ ] Symbol

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Object destructuring
const { name, age, city = 'Unknown' } = {
  name: 'John',
  age: 30
};

// Array destructuring
const [first, ...rest] = [1, 2, 3, 4];

// Template literals
const name = 'John';
const message = `Hello, ${name}!`;

// Enhanced object literals
const user = { name, age }; // Shorthand
const obj = {
  user,
  greet() { return 'Hi'; }, // Method shorthand
  [key]: value // Computed property
};

// For...of loop
for (const value of [1, 2, 3]) {
  console.log(value);
}

// Map - key-value pairs with any key type
const map = new Map();
map.set('key1', 'value1');
map.set(42, 'value2');
console.log(map.get('key1')); // 'value1'

// Set - unique values
const set = new Set([1, 2, 2, 3]);
console.log(set.size); // 3

// Symbol - unique identifier
const sym = Symbol('description');
const obj = { [sym]: 'value' };
console.log(obj[sym]); // 'value'
```

**Master When**: You use modern features naturally in your code

---

### 34. Advanced ES Features
- [ ] Proxies and Reflect
- [ ] Generators and iterators
- [ ] Async generators
- [ ] BigInt
- [ ] Optional chaining (`?.`)
- [ ] Nullish coalescing (`??`)
- [ ] Logical assignment operators
- [ ] WeakMap and WeakSet

**Key Concept**:
```javascript
// Proxies - intercept operations
const handler = {
  get(target, property) {
    return target[property];
  },
  set(target, property, value) {
    if (typeof value === 'number' && value < 0) {
      throw new Error('Only positive numbers allowed');
    }
    target[property] = value;
  }
};

const obj = new Proxy({}, handler);
obj.age = 25; // OK
obj.age = -5; // Error

// Generators - functions that can pause
function* numberGenerator() {
  yield 1;
  yield 2;
  yield 3;
}

const gen = numberGenerator();
console.log(gen.next());      // { value: 1, done: false }
console.log(gen.next());      // { value: 2, done: false }
console.log(gen.next());      // { value: 3, done: false }
console.log(gen.next());      // { value: undefined, done: true }

// BigInt - arbitrary precision integers
const big = 123456789012345678901234567890n;
console.log(typeof big); // 'bigint'
console.log(big + 1n);   // Works with bigint
```

**Master When**: You use Proxies and Generators for advanced patterns

